The paper deals with active learning of halfspaces, which is a problem in machine learning. The paper also mentions the use of online mirror descent updates, which is a technique commonly used in optimization and convex analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with label noise, which is a common problem in machine learning, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithmic framework, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
